sms.body:
WE HAVE GOT YOU COVERED
The world today is experiencing something unprecedented and we all need to stand together to fight COVID-19 and overcome these challenging times. During these testing times, we resolve to come together and exercise restraint to curb the spread. Accordingly and as mandated by the Government directive, SpiceJet has suspended all its flight operations effective March 24th, 2020 at 11:59 PM till April 14th, 2020.
Our teams are working towards cancelling the reservations of those who booked themselves for travel from March 25th, 2020 till April 14th, 2020. Upon cancellation, your entire amount will be maintained in a credit shell and the same may be used to make fresh booking and travel till February 28th, 2021 for the same passenger.
To make fresh bookings, you are requested to visit our website www.spicejet.com and at the end of the booking process, make payment using the CREDIT SHELL option. This option will be available on our website from April 1st, 2020 onwards.
Our call centre is not operational due to the nation-wide lockdown and you should be able to reach our call centre after the lockdown is called off. You may also write an email to api.request@spicejet.com. Our teams will respond to you in the earliest possible timelines. We look forward to welcoming you on-board soon.
